Description: SCREE(Single-cell CRISPR scREen data analyses and pErturbation modeling) is a workflow for single-cell CRISPR screens data processing and analysis. SCREE has two separate section: pre-process and analysis. The pre-process section is to perform reads alignment and quantification based on cellranger and cellranger-atac. The analysis section is an R package including functions of sgRNA assignment, sgRNA information visualization, single-cell quality control, perturbation enrichment ratio calculation, perturbation efficiency evaluation, regulatory score estimation and downstream functional analysis. All the outputs of SCREE can be integrated into an html file. 
